There are a few mentions of a C. D. W. Archer in the London Gazette:

<a href="http://www.london-gazette.co.uk/issues/27171/pages/1531/" rel="nofollow">6 March 1900</a>, p. 1531: &quot;War Office, 6th March, 1900. HONOURABLE ARTILLERY COMPANY OF LONDON. The undermentioned Second Lieutenants to be Lieutenants :-- [...] C. D. W. Archer. Dated 7th March, 1900.&quot;

<a href="http://www.london-gazette.co.uk/issues/27712/pages/5846/" rel="nofollow">9 September 1904</a>, p. 5846: &quot;War Office, 9th September, 1904. HONOURABLE ARTILLERY COMPANY OF LONDON [...] Lieutenant C. D. W. Archer resigns his Commission and retires into the Veteran Company. Dated 10th September, 1904.&quot;

<a href="http://www.london-gazette.co.uk/issues/30969/supplements/12556/" rel="nofollow">23 October 1918</a>, p. 12556: [War Office, 23rd October, 1918] &quot;Rly. Traffic Officers [...] Cl. HH. -- Temp. Capt. C. D. W. Archer, R.A. 4th Sept. 1918&quot;

<a href="http://www.london-gazette.co.uk/issues/32369/supplements/5081/" rel="nofollow">24 June 1921</a>, p. 5081: &quot;War Office, 24th June, 1921. REGULAR FORCES [...] Hd.-Qrs of Admin. Servs. and Depts. Rly. Traffic Officer (Cl. GG). -- Temp. Capt. C. D. W. Archer, R.A. 21st May 1921.

The <em>Army List</em> from 1901, p. 853, suggests that his full name is Charles Douglas Ward Archer: <a href="https://archive.org/details/newannualarmy1901lond" rel="nofollow">archive.org/details/newannualarmy1901lond</a>

See also: <a href="http://discovery.nationalarchives.gov.uk/SearchUI/details/C1067716?descriptiontype=Full&amp;ref=WO+339/13787" rel="nofollow">discovery.nationalarchives.gov.uk/SearchUI/details/C10677...</a>

Also Charles Douglas Ward Archer is mentioned in these editions of the London Gazette:

<a href="http://www.london-gazette.co.uk/issues/26926/pages/8/page.pdf" rel="nofollow">4 January 1898</a>, p. 8: &quot;War Office, 4th January 1898. HONOURABLE ARTILLERY COMPANY OF LONDON [...] &quot;to be Second Lieutenant [...] Charles Douglas Ward Archer. Dated 5th January, 1898.&quot;

<a href="http://www.london-gazette.co.uk/issues/34509/pages/3084/page.pdf" rel="nofollow">10 May 1938</a> p. 3084: &quot;Charles Douglas Ward Archer, Deceased. [...] Notice is hereby given that all creditors [...]
Gardens Kensington W.8 formerly of 69 Creffield Road West Acton Middlesex deceased, who died on the 27th day of February 1938 and whose Will was proved in the Principal Registry of the Probate Division of His Majesty's High Court of Justice on the 9th day of April 1938 by Vera Mary Adeline Archer and Spencer Victor Jeffery Scott the executors therein named [...] they shall not then have had notice.—Dated this 9th day of May 1938.&quot;
